      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Nausea and shaky hands are common side effects of lithium, especially when first starting the medication. It's a normal reaction, and it usually subsides within a few weeks. However, if you're experiencing severe or persistent symptoms, you should consult your doctor, as they can adjust your dosage or recommend additional treatments. In the meantime, try taking your medication with a full glass of water and eating smaller, more frequent meals to help alleviate the nausea.",
